  "title": "Construction Equipment and Machinery Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Implement and conduct construction equipment (mainly excavator and cranes) inspection and audit for infrastructure projects in Singapore (4 on-going projects)</p><p>· Diagnosing faults from company's heavy equipment</p><p>· Adjusting equipment and replacing faulty parts (for minor faults)</p><p>· Repairing damaged equipment parts if damages are minor</p><p>· Arranging and coordinating with machinery and suppliers for repairing damaged equipment, if damages are major</p><p>· Cleaning, lubricating and conducting routine services on equipment</p><p>· Reporting damaged or faulty equipment to Management</p><p>· Generate and report audit finding to Management</p><p>· Participate in major vendors / equipment assessment, selection and evaluation</p><p>· Review and evaluate projects to identify key issues and areas for improvement-develop and implement action plans to resolve issues</p><p>· Review site investigate report and provide technical input</p><p>· Other duties as assigned</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Min. 5 years' relevant working experience in equipment management</p><p>· Good communication skill</p><p>· Extensive knowledge of applicable regulations and good knowledge of equipment and machinery requirements and specifications</p>",
